issue.title: NLU Search UI
issue.body:
Create basic UI to search contents.

Basic flow is as follows:

1. User inputs search string
2. Call NLU api to get intents and entities #8 
3. Call search model with intents/entities and current search context to get new search settings.
4. Call search api with given settings to get results #13 
5. Show search results to user

issue.title: Search API
issue.body: Set up API to call with search criteria and get search results. Probably similar to existing liigo api.

issue.title: NLU Train UI
issue.body:
Simple UI to interactively use the search system #4 , view extracted intents and entities, matched search settings and search results.

Should have a button to input current query to training dataset with specified intents and entities. 
Also need "train" button to retrain model with added examples.

issue.title: Semantic Search API
issue.body:
API that takes as input the result of NLU API #8 as well as currently set search criteria and outputs a set of new search criteria that are used to call the Search API #13 

This can be defined using machine learning techniques but for the demo, hard-coded rules are sufficient. Different set of rules for each intent.

issue.title: Unsupervised Analysis and Uncover Latent attributes
issue.body:
Perform basic unsupervised clustering on the contents to uncover similar groups.

As a bonus, try to define some latent semantic tags/attributes like "Exciting", "Relaxing", "Warm", "Cold", etc and label these groups with with such tags for semantic search. 

Incase this step is finished, create an API for latent similarity search to use in conjunction with #13

issue.title: Prepare Search Dataset
issue.body:
Preprocess liigo sample dataset to use for search UI.

Required Attributes:
Title
Description
Rating
Location (latitude and longitude)
Price (yen)
Themes: (list of tags)

issue.title: Define Semantic Search Rules
issue.body:
Define a mapping from intents specified by user and the search attributes for the search UI.

For the demo we will probably hard-core the semantic search rules.

Input is current hit intent and associated entities, as well as currently set search criteria. #6 

Output are modified search criteria which are directly used to perform a new search. #13 

- Also assigned to shiki
